<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="straight-adv">straight <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /streɪt/    美 /streɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>笔直地；成直线地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The soldiers stood straight.
士兵们笔直地站着。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>An American shakes your hand firmly while looking you straight in the eye.  
美国人直视着你的眼睛，与你紧紧地握手。</p><footer>2012 安徽</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>直接；立即：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I felt very tired when I got home, and I went straight to bed. 
我到家时觉得很累，所以就直接上床睡觉了。</p><footer>2013 重庆</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll <strong>come / get straight to the point</strong>. 
我就直说了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>连续地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One of her books is the Times best-seller for 381 weeks straight.
她的一本书连续381周登上《泰晤士报》的畅销书榜。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="straight-away-off">straight away / off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>立即；马上：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I phoned my mother straight away.
我马上给妈妈打了电话。</p></div></div>